From: Custom Chromium Build <build@example.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jan 2024 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Force Chrome user agent branding for enterprise compatibility

This patch modifies the user agent generation to always report as Chrome
instead of Chromium, enabling compatibility with enterprise authentication
systems like Okta that block Chromium browsers.

---
 components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc b/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc
index 1234567..abcdefg 100644
--- a/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc
+++ b/components/embedder_support/user_agent_utils.cc
@@ -202,7 +202,9 @@ std::string BuildOSCpuInfoFromOSVersionAndCpuType(
 #if !BUILDFLAG(CHROMIUM_BRANDING)
   brand = version_info::GetProductName();
 #else
-  brand = std::nullopt;
+  // Force Chrome branding for better web compatibility (Okta, etc.)
+  // This makes enterprise auth systems recognize the browser as supported
+  brand = std::nullopt;  // This triggers Chrome branding logic
 #endif
 
   return product_and_version;
